methods.getGroupToRange:
**Incompatible overloads text - text from the first overload:**

Returns a grouping structure, possibly constructed on-demand.

*Overload 1*  
  :return: (java.util.Map<GroupingProvider.DATA_TYPE,io.deephaven.engine.rowset.RowSet>) a Map from grouping keys to Indices, or null if the group could not be constructed
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param hint: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.RowSet) - required indices within the resultant Map
  :return: (io.deephaven.base.Pair<java.util.Map<GroupingProvider.DATA_TYPE,io.deephaven.engine.rowset.RowSet>,java.lang.Boolean>) a Pair containing a Map from grouping keys to Indices, which includes at least the hint indices; and a
           Boolean which indicates that the grouping is complete
